    "body": "### Problem\n\nthe `col` of cursor position is wrong:\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/0a5add20-fd40-49e9-8b97-c07248fdabad\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. minimal.lua\n\n```lua\nvim.o.virtualedit = \"all\"\n\n\n\nvim.api.nvim_create_augroup(\"test\", {clear = true})\n\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\n\t{\n\t\t\"ModeChanged\",\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\tgroup = \"test\",\n\t\tpattern = \"n:*\",\n\t\tcallback = function()\n\t\t\tvim.o.virtualedit = \"onemore\"\n\t\tend,\n\t}\n)\n\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\n\t{\n\t\t\"ModeChanged\",\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\tgroup = \"test\",\n\t\tpattern = \"*:n\",\n\t\tcallback = function()\n\t\t\tvim.o.virtualedit = \"all\"\n\t\tend,\n\t}\n)\n\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\n\t{\n\t\t\"ModeChanged\",\n\t},\n\t{\n\t\tgroup = \"test\",\n\t\tpattern = \"i:*\",\n\t\tcallback = function()\n\t\t\tlocal pos = vim.fn.getpos(\"'^\")\n\t\t\ttable.remove(pos, 1)\n\t\t\tvim.fn.cursor(pos)\n\t\tend,\n\t}\n)\n\n-- vim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\n-- \t{\n-- \t\t\"ModeChanged\",\n-- \t},\n-- \t{\n-- \t\tgroup = \"test\",\n-- \t\tpattern = \"i:*\",\n-- \t\tcallback = function()\n-- \t\t\tvim.cmd(\"normal! `^\")\n-- \t\tend,\n-- \t}\n-- )\n```\n\n2. `nvim --clean -u minimal.lua`\n3. press `cc` `lkj` `<esc>`\n4. the statusline shows `3-4`, but should be `4` (since both `col` and `virtcol` are `4`) \n5. press `/<esc>`, the statusline shows `4`, which is correct\n\nnote:\n\nIf the third autocmd is replaced with the commented code, then in this case (`cc{text}<Esc>`) it won’t take effect, and I don’t know why\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nthe `col` of cursor should be `4`\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-1030+ge4d3812c8b\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nyes, vim 9.1\n\n### Operating system/version\n\n6.16.0-arch2-1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nst 0.8.5\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nst-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild form repo",
